article.headline: Green Bay 66, S. Utah 54
article.story: RENO, Nev. -- Alec Brown and Brennan Cougill scored 17 points apiece as Green Bay defeated Southern Utah 66-54 Friday night at the World Vision Classic. Brown also had 13 rebounds and Cougill 10 for the Phoenix (2-0), who took control of the game with a 12-0 run that put them ahead 23-8 in the first half. Keifer Sykes added 13 points and Carrington Love had 11. Jackson Stevenett led Southern Utah (0-2) with 15 points. Green Bay shot just 37.7 percent from the floor but committed only nine turnovers and outrebounded the Thunderbirds 51-40. Southern Utah, which committed 28 turnovers in a season-opening 103-65 loss to Gonzaga, had only 13 this time around. But the Thunderbirds shot 34.5 percent, including a 4 for 17 showing from 3-point range.
